# dmd
dmd (document with markdown) is a [handlebars](http://handlebarsjs.com) partial and helper pack for generating markdown API documentation (see [jsdoc-to-markdown](https://github.com/75lb/jsdoc-to-markdown) for example output). It has {{>linked-type input="module:dmd" caption="one function"}} into which you feed [jsdoc-parse](http://handlebarsjs.com) data and a template. 

The default template simply renders the [main](https://github.com/75lb/dmd/blob/master/partials/main.hbs) template, outputing all documentation and an index (if there are enough items):
```hbs
\{{>main}}
```

You can supply your own template, for example a README, and insert your API docs:
```hbs
# A Module
This is the readme for a module. 

## Install
Install it using the power of thought. 

# API Documentation
\{{>main}}
```

